solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    string licenseKeyFormatting(string s, int k) {
        string res;
        int cnt = 0;
        for (int i = s.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
            if (s[i] == '-') continue;
            if (cnt == k) {
                res += '-';
                cnt = 0;
            }
            res += toupper(s[i]);
            ++cnt;
        }
        reverse(res.begin(), res.end());
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Process the string from right to left, skipping dashes and inserting a dash every k characters. Reverse the result to correct the order. Single pass and in-place reversal keep memory and CPU usage minimal.

